  "prompt": "Is machine made egg veg or non veg?",
  "response": "Machine-made eggs, often referred to as plant-based or vegan egg substitutes, are typically made from various plant ingredients and do not come from chickens or any other animals. Therefore, they are considered vegan and are suitable for those who avoid animal products.\n\nOn the other hand, if by \"machine-made egg\" you are referring to imitation eggs that are biologically produced through artificial means but still contain actual egg components, this would classify them as non-vegetarian.\n\nIt's essential to clarify the specific context or product when discussing \"machine-made eggs\" to accurately determine whether they are considered vegetarian or non-vegetarian.",
